#: ../../../source/docs/porting/networking.rst:5
msgid "Networking"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/networking.rst:7
msgid ""
"Emscripten compiled applications have a number of ways to connect with "
"online servers. Check the subtopics here to learn about the different "
"strategies that are available."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/networking.rst:11
msgid ""
"If you are familiar with networking concepts provided by different web APIs, "
"such as XmlHttpRequest, Fetch, WebSockets and WebRTC, you can quickly get "
"started by leveraging what you already know: by calling out from C/C++ code "
"to JavaScript (see the \"Connecting C++ and JavaScript\" section), you can "
"establish networked connections by writing regular JavaScript. For C/C++ "
"developers, Emscripten provides a few approaches, described here."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/networking.rst:19
msgid "Emscripten WebSockets API"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/networking.rst:21
msgid ""
"WebSockets API provides connection-oriented message-framed bidirectional "
"asynchronous networking communication to the browser. It is the closest to "
"TCP on the web that web sites can access, direct access to TCP sockets is "
"not possible from web browsers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/networking.rst:26
msgid ""
"Emscripten provides a passthrough API for accessing the WebSockets API from "
"C/C++ code. This is useful for developers who would prefer not to write any "
"JavaScript code, or deal with the C/C++ and JavaScript language interop. See "
"the system include file ``<emscripten/websocket.h>`` for details. One "
"benefit that the Emscripten WebSockets API provides over manual WebSockets "
"access in JavaScript is the ability to share access to a WebSocket handle "
"across multiple threads, something that can be time consuming to develop "
"from scratch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/networking.rst:34
msgid ""
"To target Emscripten WebSockets API, you must link it in with a ``-"
"lwebsocket.js`` linker directive."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/networking.rst:38
msgid "Emulated POSIX TCP Sockets over WebSockets"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/networking.rst:40
msgid ""
"If you have existing TCP networking code written in C/C++ that utilizes the "
"Posix Sockets API, by default Emscripten attempts to emulate such "
"connections to take place over the WebSocket protocol instead. For this to "
"work, you will need to use something like WebSockify on the server side to "
"enable the TCP server stack to receive incoming WebSocket connections. This "
"emulation is not very complete at the moment, it is likely that you will run "
"into problems out of the box and need to adapt the code to work within the "
"limitations that this emulation provides."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/networking.rst:49
msgid ""
"This is the default build mode for Emscripten. Use the linker flag ``-"
"sWEBSOCKET_URL`` or ``Module['websocket']['url']`` to specify the WebSocket "
"URL to connect to, and the linker flag ``-sWEBSOCKET_SUBPROTOCOL`` or "
"``Module['websocket']['subprotocol']`` to control the connection type "
"(``'binary'`` or ``'text'``)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/networking.rst:56
msgid "Full POSIX Sockets over WebSocket Proxy Server"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/networking.rst:58
msgid ""
"Emscripten provides a native POSIX Sockets proxy server program, located in "
"directory ``tools/websocket_to_posix_proxy/``, that allows full POSIX "
"Sockets API access from a web browser. This support works by proxying all "
"POSIX Sockets API calls from the browser to the Emscripten POSIX Sockets "
"proxy server (via transparent use of the WebSockets API), and the proxy "
"server then performs the native TCP/UDP calls on behalf of the page. This "
"allows a web browser page to run full TCP & UDP connections, act as a server "
"to accept incoming connections, and perform host name lookups and reverse "
"lookups. Because all API calls are individually proxied, this support can be "
"slow. This support is mostly useful for developing testing infrastructure "
"and debugging."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/networking.rst:69
msgid "The following POSIX sockets functions are proxied in this manner:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/networking.rst:70
msgid ""
"``socket()``, ``socketpair()``, ``shutdown()``, ``bind()``, ``connect()``, "
"``listen()``, ``accept()``, ``getsockname()``, ``getpeername()``, "
"``send()``, ``recv()``, ``sendto()``, ``recvfrom()``, ``sendmsg()``, "
"``recvmsg()``, ``getsockopt()``, ``setsockopt()``, ``getaddrinfo()``, "
"``getnameinfo()``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/networking.rst:72
msgid ""
"The following POSIX sockets functions are currently not proxied (and will "
"not work):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/networking.rst:73
msgid "``poll()``, ``close()`` (use ``shutdown()`` instead), ``select()``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/networking.rst:75
msgid ""
"To use POSIX sockets proxying, link the application with flags ``-lwebsocket."
"js -sPROXY_POSIX_SOCKETS -pthread -sPROXY_TO_PTHREAD``. That is, POSIX "
"sockets proxying builds on top of the Emscripten WebSockets library, and "
"requires multithreading and proxying the application ``main()`` to a pthread."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/networking.rst:80
msgid ""
"For an example of how the POSIX Sockets proxy server works in an Emscripten "
"client program, see the file ``test/websocket/tcp_echo_client.c``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/networking.rst:84
msgid "XmlHttpRequests and Fetch API"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/networking.rst:86
msgid ""
"For HTTP transfers, one can use the browser built-in XmlHttpRequest (XHR) "
"API and the newer Fetch API. These can be accessed directly from JavaScript. "
"Emscripten also provides passthrough APIs to perform HTTP requests. For more "
"information, see the ``emscripten_async_wget*()`` C API and the Emscripten "
"Fetch API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/networking.rst:93
msgid "WebRTC and UDP"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/networking.rst:95
msgid ""
"Direct UDP communication is not available in browsers, but as a close "
"alternative, the WebRTC specification provides a mechanism to perform UDP-"
"like communication with WebRTC Data Channels. Currently Emscripten does not "
"provide a C/C++ API for interacting with WebRTC."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/networking.rst:101
msgid "WebTransport and QUIC"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/porting/networking.rst:103
msgid ""
"WebTransport may be used to send UDP like datagrams over QUIC. Currently "
"Emscripten does not provide a C/C++ API for interacting with WebTransport."
msgstr ""
